text: Today, I visited the African American Heritage Centering Franklin, KY. I witnessed blessings as they helped feed their community. This organization has been helping families for a number of years and everyone entering their door is welcomed with a smile and encouragement. Each month they share the gift of food to so many families. As we gather with our families this holiday season let’s recognize those that don’t have and commit to providing a kindness to someone in 2020! I know my candidacy is about restoring integrity and leadership. With leadership comes responsibility and I’m committed to save programs that feed those in need. I commit to bringing living wages to hardworking individuals and provide affordable healthcare and prescriptions so that more families can be successful and have food on their tables all year long.Thank you African American Heritage Center for your kindness and wishing you all a blessed Christmas!
